in C++, a string is usually just an array of (or a reference/points to) characters that ends with the NULL character '\0'.
A string is a 1-dimensional array of characters and an array of strings is a 2-dimensional array of characters.

Below are the 5 different ways to create an Array of Strings in C++:

a. Using Pointers
b. Using 2-D Array
c. Using the String Class
d. Using the vector Class
e. Using the array class